5000|$|Following {{the death}} of Elijah Muhammad, his son and {{successor}} Warith Deen Muhammad renamed the newspaper Bilalian News in 1981. The title was a reference to Bilal ibn Rabah, the first known black African follower of the prophet Muhammad. The renaming was part of Warith Deen's project to realign the Nation of <b>Islam</b> with <b>mainstream</b> Sunni <b>Islam.</b>|$|R
